from picl subject re cat and pregnancy in article klau klau hofmann write i hear that a certain disease toxoplasmosy be transmit by cat which can harm the unborn fetu do anybody know about it is it a problem to have a cat in the same apartment the disease you be talk about be toxoplasmosi it be a protozoan that life and multiply within cell in cat the protozoan multiply in the intestinal cell and egg be shed in the cat fece the protozoon can cro the placentum to infect the fetu the disease may be asymptomatic after the baby be bear or it may be very severe toxo may cause blindnes and mental retardation having a cat in the same apartment should not be a problem however pregnant woman should not scoop or change the cat litterbox in addition whoever do empty the litterbox should thoroughly wash hand before handle anything else especially food information come from the merck manual ed i hope thi information be helpful to you elisa 